ref-5-9                    Xerox Quintus Prolog Reference Manual                            Section 5-9: otherwiseotherwise/0 always succeeds (same as true/0).  otherwise/0 is useful for layingout conditionals (see {manual(ref-5-6)}) in a readable way.            ( test1 ->                 goal1            | test2 ->                 goal2            | otherwise ->                 goal3            )otherwise/0 has no associated error conditions.